1
00:01:31,291 --> 00:01:33,527
What do you think Ah Si is doing?

2
00:01:34,428 --> 00:01:35,696
Mr. Liu said he only got his luggage

3
00:01:35,762 --> 00:01:37,264
when he went to pick him up
at the airport.

4
00:01:37,531 --> 00:01:40,801
This guy doesn't contact us
the first day he returns.

5
00:01:41,535 --> 00:01:44,271
-Where exactly did he go?
-How would I know?

6
00:01:44,338 --> 00:01:46,940
If it were you, it would be easy to guess.

7
00:01:47,007 --> 00:01:49,776
If you didn't contact us,
then you must have gone to a girl.

8
00:01:50,544 --> 00:01:52,112
Ah Si is an idiot, though.

9
00:01:52,179 --> 00:01:53,814
He doesn't do things the normal way.

10
00:01:53,880 --> 00:01:57,317
We even came here immediately
upon receiving Zhuang's text.

11
00:01:57,417 --> 00:01:59,453
Who knew that guy would not
come home the whole night?

12
00:01:59,953 --> 00:02:01,989
Lei, what do you think?

13
00:02:03,357 --> 00:02:06,793
Maybe he went to the person
that's most important to him.

14
00:02:10,230 --> 00:02:12,933
Who's the most important person to him?

15
00:02:14,668 --> 00:02:15,836
Do you even need to ask?

16
00:02:28,715 --> 00:02:30,283
Why is your dad's pants so short?

17
00:02:30,651 --> 00:02:32,919
Short? Then wear your own clothes.

18
00:02:32,986 --> 00:02:36,023
How can someone like me
wear the same clothes two days in a row?

19
00:02:36,089 --> 00:02:37,557
That's impossible.

20
00:02:37,724 --> 00:02:40,193
That's why I gave you my dad's clothes.
You're even whining about it.

21
00:02:40,794 --> 00:02:42,696
The problem is,
does this look good at all?

22
00:02:42,796 --> 00:02:45,098
Just treat it like capri pants.

23
00:02:49,169 --> 00:02:50,937
Actually, I look quite handsome
in these clothes.

24
00:02:52,305 --> 00:02:54,041
What an egocentric pineapple head.

25
00:02:54,107 --> 00:02:55,142
I can't take it anymore.

26
00:02:55,208 --> 00:02:57,277
Wear your own clothes
and give back my dad's clothes.

27
00:02:58,211 --> 00:02:59,913
Why are you such a nag?

28
00:03:00,013 --> 00:03:01,615
I'm a man with a good "size."

29
00:03:01,715 --> 00:03:03,116
-It's "sense."
-It's "sense."

30
00:03:03,183 --> 00:03:04,551
I said that on purpose.

31
00:03:05,085 --> 00:03:08,055
These two can fight
over really petty things.

32
00:03:08,455 --> 00:03:11,591
Petty things are really
what couples fight about.

33
00:03:11,858 --> 00:03:14,728
-What?
-No, what I mean is,

34
00:03:14,795 --> 00:03:16,530
harsh words or deeds
demonstrate one's love.

35
00:03:16,630 --> 00:03:19,733
When they fight, they show
their love for each other.

36
00:03:19,800 --> 00:03:21,568
-Is that the case?
-Yes.

37
00:03:21,635 --> 00:03:24,271
Honey, then you really love me.

38
00:03:24,337 --> 00:03:26,106
Since we got married so many
years ago, until now,

39
00:03:26,173 --> 00:03:27,974
you're speaking harsh words daily,
three meals a day

40
00:03:28,041 --> 00:03:29,676
and even during supper.

41
00:03:29,743 --> 00:03:31,645
Can you not love me so much?

42
00:03:31,712 --> 00:03:33,180
I feel too much pressure.

43
00:03:33,246 --> 00:03:35,248
Don't think too much.

44
00:03:35,315 --> 00:03:37,150
I'm only saying harsh words
because you deserve it.

45
00:03:37,217 --> 00:03:39,219
-I...
-I can't say enough harsh words to you.

46
00:03:39,286 --> 00:03:41,755
-It has nothing to do with love.
-It has nothing to do with it?

47
00:03:41,822 --> 00:03:43,223
-Yes.
-Fine. Hurry.

48
00:03:43,290 --> 00:03:44,691
-Don't get mad.
-We'll be late for class.

49
00:03:44,758 --> 00:03:46,793
So what if we're late?

50
00:03:46,860 --> 00:03:49,696
You're Daoming Si. You own the school.
It doesn't matter if you're late.

51
00:03:49,796 --> 00:03:51,198
I'm different from you.

52
00:03:51,965 --> 00:03:53,667
Dad, Mom, we're going to school.

53
00:03:55,702 --> 00:03:57,003
They're sleeping so soundly.

54
00:03:58,038 --> 00:03:59,239
Let's go.

55
00:04:12,652 --> 00:04:14,054
Honey, hurry.

56
00:04:18,592 --> 00:04:19,693
Here.

57
00:04:20,193 --> 00:04:23,897
Look. The Cinderella progress chart.

58
00:04:23,964 --> 00:04:25,866
We're so ahead of schedule.

59
00:04:25,932 --> 00:04:28,869
Not only that, we've advanced so quickly.

60
00:04:28,969 --> 00:04:31,304
Our daughter can join the Olympics.

61
00:04:31,371 --> 00:04:32,739
And be the long jump champion.

62
00:04:32,839 --> 00:04:34,241
Great.

63
00:04:34,341 --> 00:04:36,676
That guy slept with our daughter
last night.

64
00:04:36,743 --> 00:04:39,279
He did spend the night at our home.
He didn't sleep with our daughter.

65
00:04:39,346 --> 00:04:40,413
It's almost the same.

66
00:04:40,480 --> 00:04:42,682
I never thought we'd be like
President Chen Shuibian.

67
00:04:42,749 --> 00:04:45,252
-Our daughter is getting married too.
-This is great!

68
00:04:45,752 --> 00:04:48,388
-We're having a wedding soon.
-I have to prepare to cry then.

69
00:04:48,455 --> 00:04:51,124
-Why should you cry?
-Because that's what people always do.

70
00:04:51,191 --> 00:04:52,692
That's how the situation becomes touching.

71
00:04:56,663 --> 00:05:00,133
I don't want to let my daughter go.

72
00:05:00,200 --> 00:05:02,135
All right, honey. Stop crying.

73
00:05:02,202 --> 00:05:05,739
I'm going to become a mother-in-law.

74
00:05:05,806 --> 00:05:09,009
I don't want to let my only beloved
daughter go too after hearing you cry.

75
00:05:10,510 --> 00:05:13,880
I never thought I'd become
a father-in-law.

76
00:05:13,947 --> 00:05:16,850
I never thought we'd become rich so soon.

77
00:05:16,917 --> 00:05:18,151
That's right.

78
00:05:20,720 --> 00:05:24,424
-Welcome, Young Master Daoming Si.
-We have class. Why are you shopping?

79
00:05:24,491 --> 00:05:27,694
-Any new arrivals? I want to wear it now.
-Of course. This way please.

80
00:05:32,032 --> 00:05:33,433
Help me choose a nice outfit.

81
00:05:33,500 --> 00:05:35,235
Why should I choose the clothes
you're wearing?

82
00:05:35,302 --> 00:05:36,436
How about this one?

83
00:05:36,503 --> 00:05:38,905
This is fresh
from our collection in Paris.

84
00:05:38,972 --> 00:05:40,207
You can try it.

85
00:05:40,307 --> 00:05:41,541
I'll try it.

86
00:05:49,516 --> 00:05:51,785
These clothes all look so expensive.

87
00:05:57,757 --> 00:05:59,025
It's NTD 58,000?

88
00:05:59,426 --> 00:06:01,261
This shirt costs NTD 58,000?

89
00:06:01,528 --> 00:06:03,430
Our family can live on that
for two months.

90
00:06:03,864 --> 00:06:05,432
Are they for real?

91
00:06:05,498 --> 00:06:08,668
It's too wasteful to buy clothes
for that amount.

92
00:06:10,971 --> 00:06:13,740
It looks so nice. It suits you.

93
00:06:14,374 --> 00:06:15,442
What do you think?

94
00:06:16,409 --> 00:06:19,179
<i>Darn. Everything suits him.</i>

95
00:06:19,246 --> 00:06:20,547
<i>How infuriating.</i>

96
00:06:20,847 --> 00:06:22,916
It looks strange.

97
00:06:25,952 --> 00:06:27,053
Is that so?

98
00:06:33,827 --> 00:06:35,228
Then how about this one?

99
00:06:35,295 --> 00:06:36,897
This one only costs NTD 120,000.

100
00:06:38,098 --> 00:06:39,299
What about this one?

101
00:06:39,966 --> 00:06:41,501
It suits you.

102
00:06:41,568 --> 00:06:43,270
You look stupid.

103
00:06:49,509 --> 00:06:50,844
Then how about this one?

104
00:06:50,911 --> 00:06:52,479
This one only costs NTD 160,000.

105
00:06:53,747 --> 00:06:54,948
It's so ugly.

106
00:06:55,248 --> 00:06:56,616
How infuriating.

107
00:06:58,618 --> 00:07:02,789
<i>Why does every single one of these
ridiculously expensive clothes suit him?</i>

108
00:07:04,190 --> 00:07:06,293
<i>Why does he care so much about what I say?</i>

109
00:07:06,860 --> 00:07:08,929
How about this one? It's nice, right?

110
00:07:11,598 --> 00:07:13,733
I think the previous one looks better.

111
00:07:15,368 --> 00:07:17,270
Are you playing a prank on me?

112
00:07:24,311 --> 00:07:25,612
I told you.

113
00:07:26,279 --> 00:07:28,248
He couldn't endure it for long.

114
00:07:29,382 --> 00:07:31,184
I just didn't think it would be this fast.

115
00:07:32,719 --> 00:07:34,754
He must really miss us.

116
00:07:34,821 --> 00:07:36,356
So much so that his hairstyle changed.

117
00:07:36,423 --> 00:07:37,457
Nonsense.

118
00:07:37,657 --> 00:07:40,260
I'm afraid you'd be too "boring"
without me.

119
00:07:40,327 --> 00:07:41,294
That's why I came back.

120
00:07:41,361 --> 00:07:43,263
It's "bored."

121
00:07:44,097 --> 00:07:45,932
Before studying English in New York,

122
00:07:45,999 --> 00:07:47,968
shouldn't you learn your Chinese well
in Taiwan first?

123
00:07:48,034 --> 00:07:49,836
Where did you go last night?

124
00:07:49,903 --> 00:07:51,905
We were at your house the whole night.

125
00:07:52,005 --> 00:07:53,707
You just arrived, and you didn't go home.

126
00:07:53,807 --> 00:07:56,276
-Where exactly did you go?
-Why are you back again?

127
00:07:56,343 --> 00:07:57,944
Shancai, why are you with him again?

128
00:07:58,011 --> 00:08:00,714
Nouveau riche, listen carefully.

129
00:08:01,047 --> 00:08:04,317
I slept at Shancai's house last night.

130
00:08:04,651 --> 00:08:05,685
You slept at Shancai's house?

131
00:08:05,752 --> 00:08:06,920
Stop talking nonsense, okay?

132
00:08:06,987 --> 00:08:08,321
Because you were jet lagged yesterday,

133
00:08:08,388 --> 00:08:09,956
and he was so dizzy he couldn't stand...

134
00:08:10,023 --> 00:08:11,758
And she looks so ugly
while sleeping, you know?

135
00:08:11,825 --> 00:08:13,960
-What are you saying?
-Shancai, this isn't true, right?

136
00:08:14,027 --> 00:08:15,695
He didn't really sleep
in your house, right?

137
00:08:19,466 --> 00:08:21,001
He really slept in my house.

138
00:08:21,067 --> 00:08:22,268
No way!

139
00:08:22,335 --> 00:08:23,670
You're kidding.

140
00:08:23,737 --> 00:08:25,538
-Let me explain.
-That's impossible.

141
00:08:25,605 --> 00:08:28,308
-How can this happen?
-Qinghe, calm down.

142
00:08:28,375 --> 00:08:29,809
I told you he was jet lagged.

143
00:08:29,876 --> 00:08:31,778
He came to my house
and my mom asked him to stay.

144
00:08:31,845 --> 00:08:33,947
-He's so thick-faced. That's what it is.
-What should I say?

145
00:08:34,047 --> 00:08:36,249
Though I forced you to drop out before,

146
00:08:36,516 --> 00:08:38,718
and did many bad things to you,

147
00:08:38,785 --> 00:08:41,755
you didn't need to tell me that
at the last minute.

148
00:08:42,922 --> 00:08:45,258
You think you're the only one
who can play mean tricks?

149
00:08:46,192 --> 00:08:48,161
Fine, you win.

150
00:08:50,864 --> 00:08:53,466
We're all good then.

151
00:08:54,834 --> 00:08:56,836
F4 is back to normal again.

152
00:08:57,871 --> 00:08:59,572
Let's go to class.

153
00:09:00,173 --> 00:09:02,275
Shancai, I'm going to class.

154
00:09:02,909 --> 00:09:05,745
Nouveau riche, don't say
she's your Shancai from now on.

155
00:09:07,213 --> 00:09:08,982
Stop crying. Are you crazy?

156
00:09:09,049 --> 00:09:11,284
Why are you crying?
Let's go to class. Come on.

157
00:09:16,389 --> 00:09:18,658
<i>I know I have many feelings</i>

158
00:09:18,725 --> 00:09:20,960
<i>that I can only keep in my memories.</i>

159
00:10:34,134 --> 00:10:36,236
You're all I think about.

160
00:10:38,171 --> 00:10:41,207
Why can't you be happy?

161
00:10:43,910 --> 00:10:47,080
Even I have someone I want to protect.

162
00:10:48,448 --> 00:10:49,449
Huaze Lei.

163
00:11:33,660 --> 00:11:34,994
I'm home.

164
00:11:41,201 --> 00:11:44,003
Mom, what happened?

165
00:11:46,573 --> 00:11:47,740
Mom.

166
00:11:48,208 --> 00:11:49,976
What exactly happened?

167
00:11:52,178 --> 00:11:56,015
Your dad borrowed NTD 1,000,000
from the loan shark.

168
00:11:57,250 --> 00:11:58,518
One million?

169
00:11:59,219 --> 00:12:03,923
And he bought lotto tickets
with that money and lost everything.

170
00:12:07,760 --> 00:12:09,963
Dad, is this true?

171
00:12:13,099 --> 00:12:15,335
I thought I would win.

172
00:12:16,903 --> 00:12:21,474
And I thought you would be marrying
into a rich family soon.

173
00:12:22,408 --> 00:12:25,111
So what if I borrow some money?

174
00:12:26,246 --> 00:12:28,481
I never thought I'd have such bad luck.

175
00:12:30,283 --> 00:12:31,751
I didn't win any prize.

176
00:12:32,485 --> 00:12:33,753
I lost all of it.

177
00:12:33,820 --> 00:12:35,822
Dad, you're too ridiculous.

178
00:12:35,922 --> 00:12:37,523
How can you do that?

179
00:12:39,792 --> 00:12:40,793
Dong.

180
00:12:41,794 --> 00:12:43,096
Let's get a divorce.

181
00:12:44,163 --> 00:12:46,132
I'll take care of Shancai.

182
00:12:46,966 --> 00:12:48,134
Mom.

183
00:12:50,903 --> 00:12:52,505
I can't take it anymore.

184
00:12:53,573 --> 00:12:55,308
I can't take it anymore.

185
00:12:55,775 --> 00:12:58,611
Never mind that we're all squeezing

186
00:12:58,678 --> 00:13:00,113
into this lousy house.

187
00:13:00,880 --> 00:13:04,050
I even usually have to pretend
to be caring

188
00:13:04,117 --> 00:13:08,254
and babysit other people's kids
to earn our living expenses.

189
00:13:09,088 --> 00:13:13,059
Now our debt suddenly
increased by one million.

190
00:13:13,126 --> 00:13:16,195
I can't take it anymore.

191
00:13:16,262 --> 00:13:18,898
Do you want us all to die?

192
00:13:18,965 --> 00:13:22,702
I... I didn't do it on purpose.

193
00:13:22,769 --> 00:13:24,904
Mom, calm down. Don't be too impulsive.

194
00:13:24,971 --> 00:13:26,172
Mom!

195
00:13:26,973 --> 00:13:29,175
I was wrong.

196
00:13:31,010 --> 00:13:32,211
Mom.

197
00:13:32,278 --> 00:13:34,914
I also don't want this to happen.

198
00:13:35,448 --> 00:13:39,652
The loan shark's interest
would kill all of us.

199
00:13:39,919 --> 00:13:43,456
And collectors from triads
would come to our house.

200
00:13:44,157 --> 00:13:47,760
We'll all commit suicide then.

201
00:13:51,197 --> 00:13:53,766
Shancai, it's all my fault.

202
00:13:54,667 --> 00:13:56,235
I'm sorry.

203
00:13:57,203 --> 00:13:59,472
Your mom is right.

204
00:14:00,406 --> 00:14:04,043
Let's... get divorced.

205
00:14:04,110 --> 00:14:07,113
-Dad.
-Don't less a useless person like me

206
00:14:07,580 --> 00:14:09,282
drag everyone down.

207
00:14:15,254 --> 00:14:16,656
No.

208
00:14:17,990 --> 00:14:21,527
Honey, I... I wasn't serious.

209
00:14:21,594 --> 00:14:23,629
Honey, I'm sorry.

210
00:14:24,263 --> 00:14:25,998
I'm sorry.

211
00:14:27,567 --> 00:14:30,903
<i>I would find a way
to get that NTD 1,000,000.</i>

212
00:14:30,970 --> 00:14:33,406
<i>Even if I lose my pride,</i>

213
00:14:33,473 --> 00:14:35,208
<i>I would surely find a way.</i>

214
00:14:43,516 --> 00:14:44,817
Miss Shancai.

215
00:14:44,884 --> 00:14:46,886
-Thank you.
-Why are you here at this time?

216
00:14:48,454 --> 00:14:49,789
There's no need. Thank you.

217
00:14:51,824 --> 00:14:53,092
What's the matter?

218
00:14:53,593 --> 00:14:56,162
Sorry to disturb you so late.

219
00:14:57,764 --> 00:15:00,032
I have a favor to ask.

220
00:15:03,302 --> 00:15:04,771
Please lend me one million.

221
00:15:06,472 --> 00:15:08,508
My dad borrowed NTD 1,000,000
from a loan shark.

222
00:15:08,875 --> 00:15:10,610
We have to return this money,

223
00:15:10,676 --> 00:15:12,812
but our living expenses
is already a problem.

224
00:15:14,080 --> 00:15:15,515
If this goes on,

225
00:15:15,948 --> 00:15:17,617
our whole family is doomed.

226
00:15:17,683 --> 00:15:19,786
I knew it. I can't take poor people.

227
00:15:20,219 --> 00:15:21,154
I...

228
00:15:21,421 --> 00:15:24,056
I may be poor, but I don't want
to borrow money from you either.

229
00:15:25,925 --> 00:15:28,161
I just have no other way.

230
00:15:29,128 --> 00:15:30,163
And I...

231
00:15:32,865 --> 00:15:34,233
I can lend you the money.

232
00:15:35,868 --> 00:15:37,203
-Really?
-Yes.

233
00:15:37,303 --> 00:15:38,704
You're lending me one million?

234
00:15:39,238 --> 00:15:40,206
NTD 1,000,000

235
00:15:41,407 --> 00:15:42,508
Thank you.

236
00:15:43,209 --> 00:15:46,345
I can't return the money
to you immediately,

237
00:15:46,779 --> 00:15:48,181
but no matter how many years it takes,

238
00:15:48,247 --> 00:15:50,116
I'd surely return the money
to you, even if gradually.

239
00:15:51,050 --> 00:15:53,486
There's a way for you
not to return the money.

240
00:15:54,454 --> 00:15:56,055
A way not to return the money?

241
00:15:56,222 --> 00:15:57,757
I really don't need to return the money?

242
00:15:58,958 --> 00:16:01,594
You don't have anything valuable
to "pawnshop" anyway.

243
00:16:02,261 --> 00:16:03,429
It's "pawn."

244
00:16:03,796 --> 00:16:04,897
It's the same.

245
00:16:05,598 --> 00:16:07,667
What is the way not to return the money

246
00:16:07,733 --> 00:16:08,701
that you mentioned earlier?

247
00:16:08,801 --> 00:16:10,536
I'm willing to do it. Tell me quickly.

248
00:16:10,603 --> 00:16:12,872
Wait for me at the alley by your house
this Saturday at 1:00 p.m.

249
00:16:12,939 --> 00:16:13,973
You'll know then.

250
00:16:14,674 --> 00:16:16,175
All right. Stop talking. Go home quickly.

251
00:16:16,242 --> 00:16:18,344
-But you...
-All right. Go home.

252
00:16:18,611 --> 00:16:20,446
I'll ask Mr. Liu to take you home.

253
00:16:21,848 --> 00:16:23,115
Go home.

254
00:16:25,251 --> 00:16:26,252
Bye.

255
00:16:45,471 --> 00:16:47,874
<i>What is Daoming Si planning?</i>

256
00:16:47,974 --> 00:16:50,176
<i>I don't need to return the one million?</i>

257
00:16:55,114 --> 00:16:56,349
Ximen.

